                            <comment id="12693758" author="mridul" created="Mon, 30 Mar 2009 14:14:11 +0100"  >
&lt;p&gt;As a workaround, you can use the hex code for &apos;.&apos; within your script.&lt;br/&gt;
Like : &apos;www\u002eyahoo\u002ecom/sports&apos; instead of trying to escape &apos;.&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But yes, the basic problem seems to exist.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12693970" author="viraj" created="Tue, 31 Mar 2009 02:44:06 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This works, as the Pig parser ignores single front slash (&amp;#41; followed by u &quot;\u&quot; &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12713313" author="milindb" created="Wed, 27 May 2009 00:00:07 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This is not an issue in Pig parsing. The Definition of a quoted string in the pig parser is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
TOKEN : { &amp;lt;QUOTEDSTRING :  &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&apos;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
(   (~[&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&apos;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;\\&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;\n&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;\r&quot;&lt;/span&gt;])
  | (&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;\\&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
      ( [&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;n&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;t&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;b&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;r&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;f&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;\\&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&apos;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;] )
    )
  | (&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;\\u&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
        [&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;0&quot;&lt;/span&gt;-&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;9&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;A&quot;&lt;/span&gt;-&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;F&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;a&quot;&lt;/span&gt;-&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;f&quot;&lt;/span&gt;]
        [&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;0&quot;&lt;/span&gt;-&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;9&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;A&quot;&lt;/span&gt;-&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;F&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;a&quot;&lt;/span&gt;-&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;f&quot;&lt;/span&gt;]
        [&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;0&quot;&lt;/span&gt;-&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;9&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;A&quot;&lt;/span&gt;-&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;F&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;a&quot;&lt;/span&gt;-&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;f&quot;&lt;/span&gt;]
        [&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;0&quot;&lt;/span&gt;-&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;9&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;A&quot;&lt;/span&gt;-&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;F&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;a&quot;&lt;/span&gt;-&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;f&quot;&lt;/span&gt;]
    )
)*
&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&apos;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt; }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It matches: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&apos;www\\.yahoo\\.com/sports&apos;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, its the stages after parsing that the regexp is getting messed up. (My suspicion is FuncSpec serialization.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12758092" author="pkamath" created="Tue, 22 Sep 2009 02:29:42 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patch which will allow define statements to treat strings the same way as strings are treated elsewhere in a pig script. So www\\..xyz&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;.com will be treated as a java string and will be sent a regex pattern where the &apos;.&apos; is escaped by a backslash to ensure it is not treated as the match-all character class. The extra backslash is to escape the backslash itself.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
